Package: trainDist
Title: Train Delay Distribution via Python (reticulate)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Wayne S.", family = "Stewart", role = c("aut","cre"),
           email = "wayne.s.stewart@ou.edu")
Description: Implements the dpqr (density, distribution, quantile, random generation)
    functions for a train delay distribution where Y in minutes has pdf f(y) = c(25 - y^2)
    for -5 < y < 5 with c = 3/500. Core math is implemented in Python for speed and
    numerical robustness, and exposed to R through 'reticulate'.
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: reticulate
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), roxygen2, devtools, knitr, rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
